column1: # The Supplement to the ISC-GEM Global Instrumental Earthquake Catalogue
# contains a list of those earthquakes
column2: not included in the main Catalogue

column1: # for which poor data availability prevented the authors from performing
# a reliable determination of either an epicentre or a magnitude or both.
# The Supplement is presented in in exactly the same format as the main Catalogue:
# - earthquake origin date and time;
# - epicentre (lat
# - error ellipse parameters (smajax
# - depth
# - Mw
# - where available: scalar moment (mo)
#   nodal planes (str1
column6: rake2) and type (BDC = best double-couple; BB = broadband analysis
column7: FM = first motion polarities; RA = relative amplitudes ; unknown if null);

column1: # - event identifier.
# Direct sources of scalar moments are currenlty gcmt (from the GCMT project
# a dedicated webpage (http://www.isc.ac.uk/iscgem/mw_bibliography.php) provides the references used.
# The epicentre or magnitude quality flag "D" indicates those poorly
# determined parameters that led to exclusion of the earthquake from the
# main list and inclusion into the Supplement.
